properties.headline: SCHEDULED ROADWORK - WOOLGOOLGA TO BALLINA Pacific Highway
properties.adviceB: Exercise caution; Allow extra travel time
properties.otherAdvice:
There will be no roadwork on the Pacific Highway between Kew and the Queensland border from 6am Friday 25 September to 6am Monday 28 September due to high traffic volumes expected for the NSW school holidays.

Likewise no work will take place from 6am Friday 2 October to 6pm Tuesday 9 October due to high traffic volumes expected for the long weekend.

Emergency maintenance and safety repair work will be carried out as required.

From Monday 28th Sept these following works will occur. Motorists can expect traffic control, reduced speed limits and short stoppages at times between 6am and 6pm:

  • There will be four days of work between Woodburn and New Italy to install traffic safety barriers and carry out earthwork, paving, drainage work, asphalting, traffic barrier maintenance and to allow access to site.  
  • There will be up to four days of work on the Pacific Highway at Mororo to remove and install signage, and to carry out asphalting.
  • There will be three days of work on the Pacific Highway between Mororo and Harwood to carry out asphalting and line marking.  
  • There will be up to four days of work on the Pacific Highway between Maclean and Tyndale and at the Maclean and Tyndale interchanges to carry out survey work, installation of signage, landscape maintenance and line marking. Motorists can expect a reduced speed limit of 60 km/h at all times.
